The paper deals with face image processing, specifically age progression and regression, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves a generative model that learns to map faces to a latent space and then project them onto a face manifold based on age, which requires machine learning techniques such as adversarial training (cs.LG) and conditional modeling (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional and deconvolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in multimedia processing (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
